# MCU Hardware & Registers

## Overview

Based on the `{{mcu}}.svd` file, this skill provides information about the peripheral registers and their fields.

## Key Peripherals

| Peripheral | Base Address | Description |
|---|---|---|
| SIM | `0x4004_7000` | System Integration Module (Clock gating, pin mux) |
| PORTA-E | `0x4004_9000`... | Pin Control Register (PCR) |
| GPIOA-E | `0x400F_F000`... | Digital I/O (PDOR, PDIR, PDDR) |
| ADC0/1 | `0x4003_B000`... | Analog-to-Digital Converter (16-bit SAR) |
| FTM0/1/2 | `0x4003_8000`... | FlexTimer (PWM, Input Capture) |
| UART0-3 | `0x4006_A000`... | Universal Asynchronous Receiver/Transmitter |
| SPI0/1 | `0x4002_C000`... | Serial Peripheral Interface |
| I2C0/1 | `0x4006_6000`... | Inter-Integrated Circuit |
| PIT | `0x4003_7000` | Periodic Interrupt Timer |

## Register Access Pattern

Use the CMSIS-provided structures (e.g., `ADC_Type`, `SIM_Type`) via base pointers:

```c
// Enable clock for ADC0
SIM->SCGC6 |= SIM_SCGC6_ADC0_MASK;

// Configure ADC0 CFG1 register
ADC0->CFG1 = ADC_CFG1_ADIV(0) | ADC_CFG1_MODE(1) | ADC_CFG1_ADICLK(0);
```

## Pin Muxing (PORT)

Configure pin function in `PORTx_PCRn`:

```c
// Enable clock for PORTB
SIM->SCGC5 |= SIM_SCGC5_PORTB_MASK;

// Set PTB0 as GPIO (MUX=1)
PORTB->PCR[0] = PORT_PCR_MUX(1);
```

## GPIO Control

- **Set Output**: `GPIOx->PDOR |= (1 << PIN)` or `GPIOx->PSOR = (1 << PIN)` (Atomic Set)
- **Clear Output**: `GPIOx->PDOR &= ~(1 << PIN)` or `GPIOx->PCOR = (1 << PIN)` (Atomic Clear)
- **Toggle Output**: `GPIOx->PTOR = (1 << PIN)` (Atomic Toggle)
- **Read Input**: `(GPIOx->PDIR >> PIN) & 1`
- **Direction**: `GPIOx->PDDR |= (1 << PIN)` (Output), `&= ~(1 << PIN)` (Input)

